<h2>Estate Planning for Murrysville Families</h2>

<p>We prepare comprehensive estate plans for Murrysville families — wills compliant with Pennsylvania's requirements under 20 Pa.C.S. § 2502, durable financial powers of attorney under 20 Pa.C.S. § 5601, advance healthcare directives, and revocable living trusts when they serve the client's goals. Murrysville's families range from young parents in the Franklin Regional School District who need guardianship provisions, to established professionals coordinating complex asset portfolios, to retirees focused on inheritance tax minimization and long-term care planning. We tailor every plan to the specific family we are working with.</p>

<p>For Murrysville homeowners concerned about whether they need a trust, we provide straightforward advice based on your actual situation — not a sales pitch. In many cases, a well-drafted will combined with properly coordinated beneficiary designations and joint ownership accomplishes the client's goals without the added expense of a trust. When a trust does make sense — for families with real property in multiple states, special needs beneficiaries, or specific distribution concerns — we explain exactly why and how it fits your plan.</p>

<h2>Probate and Estate Administration</h2>

<p>When a Murrysville resident passes, the estate is administered through the Westmoreland County Register of Wills at the courthouse in Greensburg. We guide executors and administrators through every step: filing the will, obtaining Short Certificates, publishing creditor notices in the legal journal, inventorying and appraising assets, preparing the Pennsylvania Inheritance Tax Return (REV-1500), and distributing the estate to beneficiaries. We take the time to explain each stage so that executors understand their responsibilities and avoid the personal liability that can result from procedural errors.</p>

<h2>Real Estate Closings</h2>

<p>As licensed title insurance agents through Chicago Title and First American, we handle residential closings throughout Murrysville and Westmoreland County. Our services include title searches, title insurance issuance, document preparation, settlement attendance, and deed recording with the Westmoreland County Recorder of Deeds. Whether you are buying your first home in Murrysville, selling a family property, or refinancing an existing mortgage, we ensure the transaction is handled properly from contract to closing.</p>

